hy use Polymorphism in Java?
There are a plethora of reasons to use polymorphism in Java. Some of them are mentioned below:

Code Reusability: Polymorphism allows for the creation of objects of different classes to be treated in a uniform manner, which promotes code reusability and also modularity.
By programming to a common interface or superclass, you can write a generic code that can work with multiple different objects.

